This releases the Security System, yet leaves the pistol's manual safety in the "safe" position until you are ready to release it yourself and fire the gun.Loaded Chamber IndicatorTaurus provides a loaded chamber indicator on all new compact, medium and large frame pistols. There will be SBRs and suppressors for you to check out if you are curious about them or considering getting some of your own.All we ask you to bring is eye and ear protection. Food and drink is welcome, but no alcohol will be permitted. There will be a grill available if you'd like to use it. You can bring your own paper targets if you want, but we have plenty of steel targets to shoot at. We have a plate rack, a dueling tree, and many other handgun targets set up at various distances. There will be rifle plates set up from 100 to 500 yards. Can you hit steel at 500 yards? Prove it!Safety is a big part of our club, so be prepared to hear all the same rules that you've likely already heard a million times. You will be asked to sign a liability waiver for everyone's protection. Nobody will be getting hurt at our event. Nobody will be getting muzzle-swept. Nobody will be shooting without eyes and ears. Unlike most ranges, we do allow drawing from a holster and shooting if you intend to practice that. We will have multiple stations set up in different areas for different types of shooting to keep everybody safe and comfortable. So don't be shy and join us! We are great people to hang out with. There will be beginners there as well as ex-military so don't feel like you won't fit in. $10 is a very small amount of money to shoot all day in a terrific setting such as this. We obviously aren't doing this to make money- we just pay the landowner for the privilege to shoot on his property. Our intent is to encourage people to enjoy this wonderful sport with us. Feel free to to contact me with any questions or comments, even if it's as simple as 'This sounds like fun and I'd love to join you!'.  My name is Cody and you can call or text me at REDACTED. Or email me at REDACTED. I'm looking forward to hearing from you! Check out our website to learn about us and watch some fun videos. http://rac-frag.weebly.com/
